  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'How does one describe a ceramic that uses text in its decor ?', 'Speaking', 'Extruded', 'Alandié', 'Crude', '2', 'The plate participated in the national union effort by expressing warlike, humorous or satirical accents.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%E9ramique'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'Which technique allows you to paste differently shaped elements ?', 'Barbotine', 'Reduction', 'Calibration', 'Champlevé', '2', 'The handles of a vase are for example modeled apart and then assembled to the slip on the body of the turned vase.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slip_(ceramics)'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'What is the fillet without cooking between 980° C and 1040° C ?', 'Biscuit', 'Biscotte', 'Bread', 'Cake', '3', 'The porcelain biscuit is used to make statuettes, table top and statue reductions.', ''),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'Which clay-based coating can make a ceramic smoother ?', 'Engobe', 'Estèque', 'Chamotte', 'Chandelier', '3', 'As the engobe contains loose clay, if it were laid on the dry ceramics, it would crack quickly.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slipware'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'What olive green flavor is characteristic of ancient Chinese ceramics ?', 'Celadon', 'Pernette', 'Mullite', 'Coquemar', '3', 'Celadon (literally green porcelain) refers to a color and also a type of ceramics peculiar to China and the Far East.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celadon'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'What fine, translucent ceramic is produced from kaolin ?', 'Porcelain', 'Stamping', 'Neriage', 'Albarelle', '3', 'Kaolins are white, friable and refractory clays, composed of kaolinite, or aluminum silicates.', ''),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'What dark brown Japanese e-mail is sometimes called chamois ?', 'Tenmoku', 'Dotaku', 'Nintoku', 'Daibutsu', '3', 'This e-mail is obtained by mixing feldspar, chalk, ball clay, silica, bentonite and red iron oxide (hematite).', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gla%E7ure'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'In ceramics, what is the name of the clay pellet disintegrated in water ?', 'Barbotine', 'Scraping', 'Mandrin', 'Fritte', '3', 'The decor with the slip consists of adding reliefs slip on a pottery : so called slip decorated pottery.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slip_(ceramics)'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'How many years of marriage symbolize the wedding of faience ?', '9 years old', '19 years old', '29 years old', '39 years old', '3', 'French folklore encompasses the fables, popular beliefs, fairy tales and legends of all peoples living in France.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faience'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'What is called the turntable of the potter\'s tower ?', 'Girelle', 'Rondeau', 'Cne', 'Engobe', '3', 'After arranging a clod of clay in the center of the tray, the potter centers his ground and then shakes it during his rotation.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pottery'),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'Since what year is the know-how of ceramics of art recognized in France ?', '2009', '1999', '1989', '1979', '3', 'Each state party must take the necessary steps to ensure the safeguarding of its intangible cultural heritage.', ''),
  ('en', 'Céramique et poterie', 'Which architect is known for its glazed architectural glazing ?', 'Louis Sullivan', 'Victor Bourgeois', 'Jean Welz', 'Tony Garnier', '3', 'At that time, the drawings of the American architect born in 1856 in Boston would have been impossible to execute in any other medium.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_Sullivan'),
  ('de', 'Céramique et poterie', 'Der Begriff Keramik stammt aus dem Altgriechischen « keramos » und bedeutet...', 'Keramik Erde', 'Fußabdruck', 'Formen', 'Tesson', '1', 'Das Wort erscheint in seiner modernen Bedeutung erst in der Hälfte des neunzehnten Jahrhunderts, als die Archäologie beginnt, sich für Keramik zu interessieren.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keramik'),
  ('de', 'Céramique et poterie', 'Zu welcher Keramik gehören Fayence und Terrakotta ?', 'Porös', 'Verglast', 'Fein', 'Stannifer', '1', 'Faenza, aus dem Namen der italienischen Stadt Faenza, in der es erfunden wurde, ist eine emaillierte oder lackierte Keramik mit weißem Hintergrund.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fa%EFence'),
  ('de', 'Céramique et poterie', 'Welches Material wird in der Keramik zur Lagerung von Flüssigkeiten verwendet ?', 'Grès', 'Gips', 'Céladon', 'Fluch', '1', 'Trauben, die edler als Terrakotta sind, stehen bei der Herstellung von Hochtemperaturkeramik an zweiter Stelle.', 'https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steinzeug'),
